<br>
First things first - I make clerics the leader of any group. If there are not enough clerics avaiable, I'll use 2 druids, or a druid and a shammy.  Second are players with special needs - like playing two chars. It's important to stick them in the same group since it's easier for them to keep track of themselves and their party.<br>
<br>
Second - Major tanks go with the clerics, then a secondary tank to the clerics. Then only secondary tanks (mostly paladins for that added heal) to the druid/shammy groupings.<br>
<br>
Third - Enchanters and or Bards next.<br>
<br>
Fourth - Fill in the gaps with nukers and classes with pets.<br>
<br>
In the end this makes for pretty well balanced groups.<br>
<br>
There's always exceptions - we have one tank that we always group 2 clerics with since he ALWAYS gets and maintains aggro.<br>
<br>
Don't be afraid to get bitchy, and warn them about direct tells. You're doing a job - and trying to make the best groups possible. You can't do that fast if people are pestering you.  I ususally turn off all other chats to stop my /who screen from shifting too much.<br>
 <p>~Kristallis Holyheart, 54 Vicar, officer of The Kindred Souls
