<br>
Highest Cleric - Main Heal<br>
Highest Tank - MA/MT<br>
Second Highest Tank - SA<br>
Highest Monk - Puller<br>
Another Monk - Tag Puller (me usually)<br>
Highest Druid - Secondary Heal<br>
<br>
This lets me give instructions to my Puller team, MT, SA, and the main healing team all in /groupsay. Also lets me see their health so that I can make quick decisions.<br>
<br>
The rest is pretty much as said above:<br>
Cleric, Tank, Fill in the blanks.<br>
Try to put bards into nuker heavy groups.<br>
If lots of bards try to put one per group. Their resists song/s are amazing against Nuking/AE mobs.<br>
Put in a Druid/Druid or Druid/Shaman combo if not enough Clerics.<br>
Pallies make a nice fill in for a group low on healers because of the ability to heal during downtime and LoH. Sometimes I make the SA in my Group 1 above a Pally for the ability to LoH.<br>
Always have another group available who is Healer and Tank heavy to act as backup if MA and SA go down. I often make it group 2.<br>
Allocate Main Mezzer, Crack dealer, Speed Dealer, Snarer. <br>
In some zones allocate two snarers, can never be too careful.<br>
If you can, try to even out groups so that XP should be shared around a bit. MAKE THIS THE LAST PRIORITY THOUGH !!!<br>
<br>
A raidleader channel is very useful. Password it and invite your Groupleaders, Pull team and MA/SA. It can make the raid run so much faster.<br>
<br>
Ask your raid to set to default chat the raid channel:<br>
/channel chat name_of_channel<br>
<br>
Change the colour of your chat text and tell your whole raid how to do it before you begin.<br>
<br>
/usercolor XX RR GG BB<br>
XX = 36 - 45 (for channel 1 to 10)<br>
RR/GG/BB = Red/Green/Blue<br>
<br>
Go to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.speakeasy.org/~sherih/EQ/rgbcolors_tai.htm">www.speakeasy.org/~sherih/EQ/rgbcolors_tai.htm </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to see a list of colours.<br>
<br>
