Actually, that's actually a good system-and from everything I've heard about Shabbate, the raids go off very well. When I was leading raids I went by the skill of those I knew above all else. From there I used levels as a determining factor and tried to balance the groups. Whenever I raided Vox I would have the 'Chanter Love' group. Three Enchanters and three 51+ druids. One Druid assigned to each Enchanter personally for heals. If I had the Paladins to spare, I would put one in the 'Chanter Love' group for the LoH in case heals weren't going off fast enough. <br>
